dslRuleAfterChange:
For a hypothetical DSL extension:

// Rule for List iteration
for (int $i = $initial; $i $op $limit; $i $inc) {
    $Type $element = $collection.get($i);
    $body$
}
=>
for ($Type $element : $collection) {
    $body$
}
;;

// Rule for Array iteration
for (int $i = $initial; $i $op $limit; $i $inc) {
    $Type $element = $array[$i];
    $body$
}
=>
for ($Type $element : $array) {
    $body$
}
;;

Note: The actual implementation would be more complex to handle various initializers, conditions, and incrementors, and ensure correct replacement of usages of '$i' or '$element_from_get_or_array_access' within '$body$' if they are not explicitly declared/assigned at the beginning.

